---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QRGenerator from '../../components/QRGenerator.jsx';
import RelatedTools from '../../components/RelatedTools.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="QR Code Generator Free – Create QR Codes Instantly"
  description="Generate QR codes for any URL, text, email or phone number. Download as PNG. No watermark, no login, completely free. Works in your browser."
>
  <div class="tool-page">
    <div class="tool-header">
      <a href="/categories/developer-tools/" class="back-link">← Developer Tools</a>
      <h1 class="tool-title">QR Code Generator</h1>
      <p class="tool-subtitle">Generate a QR code for any URL, text, email, phone number or Wi-Fi password. Download instantly as PNG.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ad-slot ad-slot-horizontal">
      <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" data-ad-slot="1234567890" data-ad-format="auto" data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
      <script is:inline>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
    </div>

    <QRGenerator client:load />

    <div class="ad-slot ad-slot-horizontal" style="margin-top: 32px;">
      <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" data-ad-slot="0987654321" data-ad-format="auto" data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
      <script is:inline>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
    </div>

    <section class="seo-content">
      <h2>How to create a QR code</h2>
      <p>Type or paste any URL, text, email address or phone number into the input field. Your QR code generates instantly as you type. Customize the size and foreground color, then download the QR code as a PNG image file — ready to use in print, digital or social media.</p>

      <h2>What can I encode in a QR code?</h2>
      <p>QR codes can encode any text string: website URLs, plain text messages, email addresses (prefix with "mailto:"), phone numbers (prefix with "tel:"), SMS messages, vCard contact information and Wi-Fi credentials. The most common use is encoding a URL so that scanning the QR code opens a website directly in the camera app.</p>

      <h2>Where are QR codes used?</h2>
      <p>Business cards linking to a LinkedIn profile or portfolio. Restaurant menus accessed by scanning a table code. Event tickets and boarding passes. Product packaging linking to instructions or promotional content. Marketing materials and posters linking to landing pages. Store windows allowing contactless access to an online shop. Museum exhibits linking to audio guides or extended information.</p>

      <h2>How large should a QR code be for print?</h2>
      <p>A good rule of thumb is that the QR code should be at least 2 cm × 2 cm (about 0.8 inches square) for reliable scanning at typical reading distances. For billboards or large-format printing, scale up proportionally. The scanning distance should not exceed 10× the size of the QR code — a 3 cm code is readable from up to 30 cm away.</p>

      <h2>Is the QR code free with no watermark?</h2>
      <p>Yes. Completely free, no watermark, no account, no usage limits. Generate as many QR codes as you need.</p>
    </section>

    <RelatedTools slugs={["password-generator", "base64", "color-picker"]} />
  </div>
</Layout>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebApplication",
  "name": "QR Code Generator",
  "url": "https://www.pixmidas.com/tools/qr-code/",
  "applicationCategory": "UtilitiesApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "Any",
  "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript",
  "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD" },
  "description": "Free QR code generator. Create QR codes for any URL, text, email or phone number. Download as PNG, no watermark."
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do I create a QR code for free?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Type or paste any URL, text, email address or phone number into the input field. Your QR code generates instantly as you type. Customize the size and color, then download as a PNG image." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What can I encode in a QR code?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "QR codes can encode website URLs, plain text, email addresses (mailto:), phone numbers (tel:), SMS messages, vCard contact info, and Wi-Fi credentials. The most common use is encoding a URL to open a website directly from a camera scan." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How large should a QR code be for printing?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "At least 2 cm × 2 cm (about 0.8 inches square) for reliable scanning at typical reading distances. A 3 cm code is readable from up to 30 cm away. Scale up proportionally for billboards or large-format printing." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is the QR code generator free with no watermark?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Completely free, no watermark, no account required, no usage limits. Generate as many QR codes as you need." }
    }
  ]
}
</script>
